      "comment": "BRINDLE SURPRISE (1) beaten last start over the 435m at Sale but finished in the minors in a slick 24.48. Hard to top on the time from last start. OVERLAND BOY (2) caught the eye when clocking a dominant 30.78 over 545m at Ballarat. Harder here but will be in this for a long way. ZIPPING ANDORA (5) goes very well this course and distance starting seven times for three wins and two minors. Missed the frame latest (38.09) when fourth over 660m at Bendigo in a Grade 4/5. With even luck and a clean start should be thereabouts. MOTOR CITY ROSSI (4) placed last time at big odds - worth some thought.",
